comments.text:
+ConceptSoup It's difficult to point out in one summary. But on the 
surface, his songs are fast, swear spewing, rage filled rhymes that aim to 
take down artists, or to complain about some aspect of social life whether 
that be parenting, or censorship of music. However, there is something that 
i've discovered in his songs that are way deeper than all that. Although 
he's doing all the things I said above, I find that most of the deeper 
meanings are about him struggling to get by with being famous, and being a 
father, and a whole lot of the songs are about telling his listeners to not 
be like him, and to live your life to the fullest. It's strange to hear it 
from someone if you can't find the meanings yourself I know. I've got a 
soft spot for Eminems music, although I don't listen to it much anymore. 
When I was in highschool, believe it or not, listening to Eminems music 
brought me out of depression, helped me turn away friends who tried to get 
me to do all kinds of drugs with them, and generally really actually molded 
my personality into what it is today. I know people are going to call me a 
dick rider and shit, but I don't care, it's the truth. I would argue that 
Eminems music has had one of, if not the biggest impact on me of anything 
in my life.
comments.author: The Spectator

comments.text:
+MINUS DA GREEZ Thank you! But you don't have to apologize. I understand it 
is very easy to believe he was guilty. There is so much garbage trown over 
his head. If you don't look in to it you tend to believe it. But if you, as 
you said, was a big fan of his. I recomment you reading books like Man in 
the music. And Michael Jackson the conspiracy (even though I didn't read 
the last one but I hear good things about it). Because you are going to 
understand his stand on this and where he came from. I'd like to thank you 
for your answers. You are the only person who is willing to have a grown up 
conversation about this ;-) You don't have to agree with me.. that is fine. 
But don't throw him away immediatly. He has done wonderful things and he 
was acquitted.. so in fact he was innocent. What people think after the 
trial is their bussiness. But he was acquitted..
comments.author: Arla Brandsma

comments.text:
+Arla Brandsma i respect your argument..and you obviously are a very warm 
person ...so im gonna apologise to you if any of my remarks have upset or 
made you feel any bad feeling ...i really do hope your right ...and i know 
nothing with the media is hundred per cent ..just things he did and ways he 
acted just caused a lot of questions...but i respect you very so much and 
your argument ...he loved his fans that was clear ...and you are an example 
why....bless you :)
comments.author: MINUS DA GREEZ

comments.text:
+MINUS DA GREEZ
He also was acquitted of the 'jesus juice' thing..
And no I would have a good talk with an adult who'd share his bed with my 
kid.
But I believe that there was no sexual involvement in that action. I think 
it was creating a cozy space where they could watch movies and eat cookies 
in bed. As I said. I'm not here to defend MJ, i agree with you that some 
things he admitted doing wasn't something I would choose to do. But hey.. 
there might also be a lot of things you would do and I wouldn't and the 
other way around. You know the only evidence they had was the story of a 
few little kids wich we know the parents had a history of fraud, the kids 
didn't show up in court. We have tapped phonecalls of a father who admits 
he just wanted the money and wanted to destroy MJ even though he knew his 
kid wasn't molested. So is there in fact ANY evidence. Nope........ 
therefore.. he was acquitted. And correct so! It's so sad people still want 
to believe the things he was accused of. If someone accused me of a murder 
and I never did it, there was no evidence and I was acquitted and the whole 
world still believes I commited the crime.. thats wrong.. why would that be 
any difference with Michael Jackson. Because he's famous and was somewhat 
eccentric? Wow.. great analysis than.. You can't just accuse someone 
because he was different? We made him different.. He was different, and I 
loved it. Everybody loved it, untill those crazy stories just added up.. 
'Just because you read it in the magazine or seen it on the tvscreen don't 
make it factual'
comments.author: Arla Brandsma

comments.text:
+Arla Brandsma i do sort of understand ...but im a father and i wouldnt at 
all agree with any adult getting into bed with my children or giving them

comments.author: MINUS DA GREEZ

comments.text:
+MINUS DA GREEZ I agree he had some strange behaviour from time to time. 
But you have to admit that he was pushed in a strange life ;-) Because of 
people who liked him or hated him or wanted money from him. He never was a 
kid, when he was 10 years old he was working in the studio while across the 
road, in the park, some kids his age were playing soccer. He wanted to join 
them so bad but he couldn't. He bought classmates candy just to be with 
him. His life was hard.. he couldn't go to a public movietheater but he had 
the money so he created one in his garden. Why not? He wanted to be able to 
go to the cinema just like everybody else. Children were the only kind of 
people that did not see him as the king of pop, they were the only people 
who did not betray him.. until the parents took advantage of his innocence 
and naivety That is sad.. Don't forget he was acquitted for any 
wrong-doing. (and I'm sorry if I misspelled a lot of words.. I do my best 
but I'm Dutch so I apologize in advance ;-))
